In his order, the Assistant Commissioner of Police, Falaknuma, further said, â€œthe area contains a mixture of population and there is every chance of developing communal tension and may lead to law and order problem due to event or during the eventâ€.

Hashmi said, â€œthe right to protest is part of my fundamental right given to every Indian citizen as per the Indian constitution.â€ He added that he intends to protest peacefully as he believes that CAA is a serious violation of the Indian constitution and against the countryâ€™s secular values.

The city has recently witnessed an Anti-CAA â€˜million marchâ€™, a â€˜Tiranga Rallyâ€™ and several smaller protests against the new law. Several protests were foiled by the city police as permission was denied citing the Law and Order as well as Traffic issues.

